    "reviews": [
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2022-01",
        "text": "Jesse of Two Elk Studios provided a wonderful birthday experience for my friends and me. I appreciated his professionalism and talent for connecting, remembering names, and creating a delightful experience. The photos themselves were gorgeous, and that was not an easy feat; he was taking photos of nine ordinary (read non-model) people. However, what set Jesse's service apart was how he handled both a challenge and a misunderstanding. He was the height of graciousness in both situations. Anyone can look at Two Elk Studios' work and see that their images are phenomenal, but I wanted to highlight the level of service clients receive as well. 5/5 stars!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2020-09",
        "text": "We hired Two Elk Studios to photograph our Welcome Party the night before our wedding, and we also hired them for the day of our wedding for a fun interactive photo wall! Jesse was the photographer for our Welcome Party, and he did a beautiful job. The photos are great! Jesse was also the attendant of our interactive photo wall at our wedding the following day, which was a huge hit with all of our guests! It was so much fun. He provided a great backdrop I picked out, and he assisted guests in sending digital prints to themselves of their photos, as well as had copies printed for each photo and put into a photo guest book that we purchased from him as well. Thank you Jessie and Two Elk for your services and capturing our Welcome Party and being so attentive at the photo wall at our wedding!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2019-06",
        "text": "Working with Jesse has been an incredible experience.  He is extremely easy to work with and you can tell he loves what he does.  It was wonderful getting to meet him prior to our wedding to do the engagement photo shoot so that when it came time for wedding day, we could look natural as he did his work.  He has a great blend of artistic vision and making sure to capture the energy of the event.  I highly recommend Two Elk Studios to anybody looking to capture the magic of their wedding."
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2018-03",
        "text": "I worked with Jesse for a commercial shoot for my suit company, Bespoke Edge, and I couldn't be happier with the images!\n\nBefore the shoot, Jesse had scouted specific locations to best take advantage of the natural light and at what time of day. I've worked with many photographers over the years and I was very impressed by Jesse's eye for posing and lighting.\n\nIt was such a great experience working with Jesse and Two Elk Studios; the photos were just what my team and I needed!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2022-01",
        "text": "I've had the pleasure of working with Jesse on a few different occasions. The first occasion was a family photo session with my wife, 2 year old  son, and 2 big dogs. Jesse was amazing at getting our kiddo to smile and laugh while helping us get the dogs just right too. In all of this he was calm, light hearted and captured amazing photos. Some perfectly proper and some fun candid shots as well!\n\nThe print products he offers are high quality and not something you can get from an online print site. He even worked with us to edit and print some of our own photos from previous adventures.\n\nToday I needed a headshot for a professional event. I called Jesse and he was able to squeeze me in for a visit to his studio, shoot the photos edit,  and get it to me in the same day for the publication! Amazing!  I have to add that the experience for the headshot was just as fun yet done in a very professional manner with great direction to ensure a quality photo.\nOnly complaint is that I don't look younger in the photo. :) I can't blame him... he's a photographer and not a magician!\nThanks Jesse!"
      }
    ]
  },
